Program #13

1) Write a program to create a file and write data into it using the methods OutputStream class.

2) Get the data (the input text to write) from the user. - 
    Specify only 50 bytes (about 2 lines). You can also
    specify for the user to press enter after each line to get input into the program.
    
3) Write the input text into a file called “output.txt”. -
    Read the written text from the file “output.txt” using an
    inputStream and write its content to the monitor.
    
4) Watch the video assignment 13 posted on Blackboard for a demo and more -
    explanation of what the program should do.
